race.comment: TILES AND WINE (1) comes off an average performance last start when seventh at Healesville over 350m behind Ponting (20.42) in a Grade 5. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. VELOX BALE (2) jumped from the inside and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten one length (25.78) behind Penguin Pat at Ballarat. Bold showing expected. SHIMA BALLAD (5) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (26.70) in a T3 RSTW at this track. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Expected to give a good account. SUPERFLY GIRL (7) did a good job to finish second last time out over 350m at Healesville (19.79) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot.
